select max(file_id) from ( select file_id from ( select l.file_id from CTL_INPUT_FILES_LOG l inner join ( select a.* ,max(case when STATUS_CD = '3' then file_id else 0 end) over (partition by FILE_TYPE_CD) max_3 from CTL_INPUT_FILES a where source_name in ('CRM') ) i on i.file_id = l.file_id inner join CTL_ACTUAL_FILE_TYPES a on trim(upper(i.FILE_TYPE_CD)) = trim(upper(a.FILE_TYPE_CD)) where l.STATUS_CD = 1 and l.file_id > i.max_3 group by l.file_id --count attemp having count(*) > 10 ) where rownum < 2 union all select -1 from dual )
select nvl(max(file_id),-1) file_id from ( select file_id from CTL_INPUT_FILES_LOADING where status_cd='1' and source_name='CRM' and rownum<=1 union all select null from dual )
